Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450}(lengthways into 1cm slices), then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest the @lemon{1/2} and cut into wedges. Peel and grate the
@garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10} and the
@dried oregano{1} with half the garlic and the @salt{1/4%tsp} and
@water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British pork mince{240}.

Season with pepper and mix together with your hands. Shape into small sausage
shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas and pop them onto another
baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the chips are halfway through cooking, turn them and return to the oven.

At the same time, pop the kofta tray on the top shelf and bake until browned on
the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways
into small pieces.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks)
and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

In a medium bowl, combine the @olive oil{1%tsp} and half the lemon juice.
Season with salt, pepper and @sugar{1%tsp}.

Toss the tomatoes and cucumber in the dressing and set aside.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50} into small pieces.

Pop the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75} into a small bowl with half the mint,
lemon zest and remaining garlic (add less if you don't love raw garlic). Season
with salt and pepper, then mix together.

A few mins before the koftas are cooked, pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2}
(1 per person) into the oven to warm through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Just before serving, mix the Greek style salad cheese and remaining mint into
the salad.

To serve, pop a flatbread onto each plate, then pile the chips, salad, koftas
and mint yoghurt on top. Serve any remaining chips and lemon wedges alongside.

Enjoy!